"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-comment-podcasts-paris-2024-olympics-uk-team-tom-cruise-closing-ceremony-b1176112.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Comment|Podcasts  Listen here on your chosen podcast platform.  After an incredible two weeks, theParis Olympicshas officially come to an end.  There is no denying that theGamescaptured the world once again and gifted us countless iconic sporting moments, but did Paris 2024 deliver everything it promised?  The Evening Standard's Sports Correspondent, Matt Majendie, joins us from Paris to give his verdict, and share his favourite sporting moments from the 2024 Olympics.  In part two, our Arts Correspondent, Robert Dex, gives his review of the star-studdedclosing ceremony, and discusses some ofthe most talked about moments from the Games.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"